my re\nturn has passed both houses, and\nIb ready for the president's sig\nnature. The general Impression\nseems to be that these two great\nfactors, which will provide means\nfor transporting freight and pas\nsengers, point the way to unusual\nadvantages for this particular sec\ntion of th* country.\"\nRead Au* Marks* aad Grot try\ni p-g* today.\nTBI TAOOMA THOU\nSHOT BY AIRGUN\nStruck in the forehead by the\nshot from an air-gun fired by the\n10-year-old son of MY. and Mrs.\nJ. T. Mulcahey, 809 North M St.,\nlittle 3-year-old Samuel Strong,\nson of Mr. and Mrs. S. F. Strong,\n819 North M street, was slightly\nwounded yesterday.\nMtoK mom i_\u00bb\nbis urn siqbj _Af^A\nllkl MmllliMiri I\nJn^WJWnMj^^*T|_\"B j A\nPAVE BOULEVARD\nA new road district was estab\nlished by the county commission\ners yesterday afternoon In order\nto pave tbe Mt. Tacoma boulevard\nthis summer for a distance of 6.34\nmil**.\nOLOF BULL SUES\nStruck by a cable car at 13th\nand C streets several months ago,\nOlof Bull, the well known violin\nist, has started actio nfor $10,000\ndamages against the T. R. A P.\naampany In superior court.\nMONDAY HOLIDAY\nBecause Washington's birthday\nfalls on Sunday, tbe day will be\ngenerally observed Monday, pub\nlic school*, banks, and all public\nbuildings being closed on that\nday.\nLADBBB* CLOAKS AXD BCITH\nGreenbaums'\n1189 O Street.\nAll Flooded\nLOS ANGELES, Feb. 20. A\ndeling* that brought eight Inches\nof rain In half a day caused the\nlosa of three lives and the de\nstruction of $1,000,000 worth of\norange orchard* ln Southern Cali\nfornia.\nTo Bring Suit\nThe suit of the Oreat Northern\nand Northern Pacific to stop the\nstate from taxing them on \"good\nwill\" will bring up a lot of inter-'\nesting issues ln the state courts.\nPAOETH-UEB.\nThe companies claim they should\nbe exempt from taxation on any\ngood will. Otherwise they Insist\nthey should be allowed credit for\ngood will in the valuation for rat*\nfixing.\nEYES EXAMINED RIGHT\nCASWELL OPT